  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Enhancing Services and Linkages for Children affected by HIV and AIDS (ELIKIA ) activity is to strengthen comprehensive care and support for OVC who are infected and affected by HIV, increasing their chances to grow up to be healthy, educated, and socially well-adjusted adults. This activity will clearly support the PEPFAR continuum of care in DRC by: co-locating in priority health zones served by USAID, CDC, and DOD clinical programs; referring participating families to HIV services for which they are eligible; and receiving referrals of eligible families from clinical partners especially around PMTCT and pediatric care and treatment in 3 focus provinces  and Bas-Congo (pending final decision from PEPFAR). The following objectives contribute to this overarching goal: 1:  Reduced economic vulnerability of target households so that they can better provide for the essential needs of the children in their care; 2:  Increased utilization of essential services among target orphans and other vulnerable children and their households.and 3:  Strengthened GDRC provincial and district social welfare systems. A multi-component approach with a focus on linking OVC services to clinical services in the three provinces will be undertaken to address the antecedents of risk of OVCs. Programmatic approaches include, but are not limited to the following: dual beneficiary targeting (at clinical and community levels), beneficiary graduation and exit strategy, gender-sensitive, family-centered and age-appropriate approaches.The pivot strategy is the implementation of effective and efficient household economic strengthening interventions such as village saving association loans coupled with parenting skills to enable parents and/or caregivers to wisely invest in child wellbeing.</narrative>
  </description>
